OL,3,C'They were human beings': Asylum
OL,4,Cseekers must be 'at the heart' of
OL,5,CManston probe
OL,7,FJesse Nicholls, counsel representing
OL,8,FDuncan Lewis Solicitors and Deighton
OL,9,FPierce Glynn Solicitors on behalf of a
OL,10,Fnumber of those detained at the
OL,11,Fcentre, said: "The mistreatment of our
OL,12,Fclients at Manston and the deplorable
OL,13,Fconditions to which they were subject
OL,14,Fhad the effect of dehumanising them.
OL,16,F"That dehumanisation should not be
OL,17,Freinforced and compounded by
OL,18,Fcharacterising our clients and others
OL,19,Fby their immigration status ` they
OL,20,Fwere people, human beings, their
OL,21,Fexperiences matter. They matter.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/8
